Report: act_report¶

WeRateDogs Twitter Data wrangling task¶

Data analysis has always been a fascinating skill area which allows all data to be gathered from all sources, assessed and cleaned and then explored to produce fascinating analysis and visualizations.

Data that was gathered with a lot of quality and tidiness issues can be transformed into beautiful dashboards, visualizations and meaningful reports for various reports.

Research Questions¶

  1. What were the most popular breeds predicted by the image prediction model?

  2. What was the most popular dog stage in the twitter_archive dataframe?

  3. Were the ratings affected by the retweet counts and favorite counts?

  4. Which year has the most tweets?

  5. How has retweet count changed over the years?

Insight 1¶

A scatter plot of year against retweet count

2016 is the year with the highest retweet counts and 2015 had very low retweet counts in comparison.

Insight 2¶

The most popular dog stage was pupper, closely followed by doggo and floofer is the least popular dog stage. Puppers were most popular.

Insight 3¶

Although, 12 is the most occuring rating in the master twitter_archive dataframe, 13 is the rating with the highest number of retweet counts and favorite counts.

Insight 4¶

Most of the dogs (almost in 50:50 ratio) in the dataframe do not have names. We do see that the names Bo, Sampson, Oliver and Loki are the most popular names in comparison to the others.

Insight 5¶

The top two most popular breeds predicted by the image prediction model are Labrador retriever and the Golden retriever.

Limitations¶

1.The data had a lot of zero values and null values

2.redundant data and timestamping issues

3.rating above 10 are unrealistic
